subsection.def:
prescribed
                    (訂明) means provided by regulations made under
                    section 23;

paragraph.content:
a registered midwife to be nominated by the Hospital Authority within the
                    meaning of the Hospital Authority Ordinance (Cap.
                        113);

a registered midwife to be nominated by each hospital declared by the
                    Council under regulations made under this Ordinance to be a training school for
                    midwives;

has completed such training as may be prescribed and has passed such
                    examinations as may be required by the Council;
                    or

has been guilty, in Hong Kong or elsewhere, of unprofessional conduct;
                    (Amended 67 of 1985 s.
                        16)
